{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17603287","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17603287"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:35:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:35:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15733"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15733","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15733"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.31,0.22,0.25,0.17,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8424"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67276"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8424","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8424"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15733"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52728"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1793"},{"type":"tags","id":"4111"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5247"},{"type":"tags","id":"5303"},{"type":"tags","id":"7037"},{"type":"tags","id":"8137"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20278"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20281"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22522"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67276","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67276"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe combined oral contraceptive pill (OCP) has various effects on cancer risk in women.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the effect on the risk of ovarian cancer?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Decreased risk of endometrioid and clear cell ovarian cancers","Decreased risk of endometrioid but increased risk of clear cell ovarian cancers","Increased risk of both endometrioid and clear cell ovarian cancers","Increase risk of endometrioid but decreased risk of clear cell ovarian cancers","No effect on either endometrioid or clear cell ovarian cancers"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecombined oral contraceptive pill decreases the risk of both endometrioid and clear cell ovarian cancers\u003C/strong\u003E. This protective effect has been well-documented in multiple large epidemiological studies. The risk reduction is approximately 50% after 5 years of use.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt is incorrect that the pill would have \u003Cstrong\u003Edifferent effects on endometrioid versus clear cell cancers\u003C/strong\u003E, as both of these subtypes share similar risk factors and pathogenesis. The suggestion that OCPs would \u003Cstrong\u003Eincrease risk\u003C/strong\u003E of these cancers is also incorrect - the protective effect is one of the well-established non-contraceptive benefits of the pill. It is also incorrect that OCPs would have \u003Cstrong\u003Eno effect\u003C/strong\u003E on ovarian cancer risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe protective effect persists for decades after discontinuation of the pill. The longer the duration of use, the greater the risk reduction.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Combined oral contraceptive pill use reduces risk of both endometrioid and clear cell ovarian cancers","The protective effect of combined oral contraceptive pills against ovarian cancer persists for decades after discontinuation"],"references":["Kamani M, Akgor U, G\u00fcltekin M. Review of the literature on combined oral contraceptives and cancer. Ecancermedicalscience. 2022 Jun 23;16:1416. doi: 10.3332/ecancer.2022.1416. PMID: 36072240; PMCID: PMC9377820.","Momenimovahed Z, Tiznobaik A, Taheri S, Salehiniya H. Ovarian cancer in the world: epidemiology and risk factors. Int J Womens Health. 2019 Apr 30;11:287-299. doi: 10.2147/IJWH.S197604. PMID: 31118829; PMCID: PMC6500433","Cho KR, Shih IeM. Ovarian cancer. Annu Rev Pathol. 2009;4:287-313. doi: 10.1146/annurev.pathol.4.110807.092246. PMID: 18842102; PMCID: PMC2679364","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52728"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15733"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52728","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52728"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-04T14:55:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-04T14:56:08+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8424"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67276"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":